quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,37,"Then Adam received from his Lord Words.{1} And his Lord pardoned him (accepted his repentance). Verily, He is the One Who forgives (accepts repentance), the Most Merciful.",footnotes:1:(V.37): These words are mentioned in the Qur’ân; (7:23): They are: "Our Lord! We have wronged ourselves. If You forgive us not, and bestow not upon us Your Mercy, we shall certainly be of the losers."
  2,38,"We said: "
  2,39,"But those who disbelieve and belie Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) - such are the dwellers of the Fire. They shall abide therein forever."